## Part 1 — Secret backend helpers added near top of 13_reverse_proxy.sh (line ~23)

vault.env loader:
  [[ -f "$ZOOLANDIA_CONFIG_DIR/vault.env" ]] && source "$ZOOLANDIA_CONFIG_DIR/vault.env"

New functions (in order of definition):
  _zl_keyring_available()    — checks DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS or /run/user/<uid>/bus socket
  _zl_ensure_secret_tool()   — installs libsecret-tools via apt if secret-tool missing; prompts first
  _zl_get_backend()          — reads ~/.config/zoolandia/secret_backend; defaults keyring if D-Bus up
  _zl_save_backend()         — writes backend choice to secret_backend file
  _zl_vault_path/write/read/delete()  — Vault KV helpers (path: secret/zoolandia/dns/<key>)
  _zl_secret_write()         — dispatches to keyring/file/vault; graceful fallback chain
  _zl_secret_read()          — dispatches; keyring falls back to file on miss/absent secret-tool
  _zl_secret_delete()        — clears from all three backends simultaneously
  ensure_vault()             — installs Vault CLI via Ansible, prompts VAULT_ADDR, handles auth
  show_secret_backend_menu() — dialog picker; calls ensure_vault if vault selected

