## Part 2 — configure_clouddns() rewrite

Old behaviour:
  - Read: cat "$SECRETS_DIR/clouddns_client_id"
  - Write: echo ... > file; chmod 600
  - Delete: rm -f

New behaviour:
  - Read:   _zl_secret_read "clouddns_client_id"
  - Write:  _zl_secret_write "clouddns_client_id" "$client_id"
  - Delete: _zl_secret_delete "clouddns_client_id"
  - Display masked: "****${value: -4}" (last 4 chars visible)
  - New menu item: "Storage Backend" → show_secret_backend_menu
  - Post-save: dialog --yesno "Saved. Run API test now?" → test_clouddns_api
  - Client Secret input switched to --passwordbox (value not echoed)
  - --passwordbox now passes "$current_secret" as init so pressing OK preserves existing

