================================================================================
## BUGS FOUND AND FIXED IN THIS SESSION
================================================================================

BUG 1: Client Secret dialog always empty on edit
  Root cause: --passwordbox called without init value; if user hit OK empty string returned,
              [[ -n "$client_secret" ]] guard blocked save entirely.
  Fix: pass "$current_secret" as 4th arg to --passwordbox. Field appears blank (by design)
       but OK-without-typing returns existing value.
  File: modules/13_reverse_proxy.sh, configure_clouddns() "Client Secret" case

BUG 2: GNOME Keyring missing from backend menu
  Root cause: _zl_keyring_available() required `secret-tool` to be pre-installed.
              libsecret-tools is not in default Ubuntu install, so check always failed
              even with live D-Bus session.
  Fix: split into two functions:
    _zl_keyring_available() — D-Bus check only (shows option in menu)
    _zl_ensure_secret_tool() — installs on demand at first write attempt
  Also fixed: _zl_secret_read() used bash ;& fall-through which cannot be conditional;
              replaced with explicit `if command -v secret-tool` guard.
  File: modules/13_reverse_proxy.sh

